# Use Commerce Dev MCP

The `adobe-commerce-dev` MCP provides GraphQL schema introspection for Adobe Commerce.

## No authentication required

This MCP works offline against a bundled Commerce GraphQL schema — no Commerce instance,
API keys, or network access needed.

## This project's Commerce endpoint

- **Commerce URL:** {commerceEndpoint}
- **Store view:** {storeViewCode}

## Available tools

| Tool | Description |
|---|---|
| `introspect_admin_schema` | Introspect the Commerce Admin GraphQL schema |
| `introspect_storefront_schema` | Introspect the Storefront GraphQL schema |
| `get_type` | Get the definition of a specific GraphQL type |

## Example

```
> adobe-commerce-dev::introspect_storefront_schema
> adobe-commerce-dev::get_type name="ProductInterface"
```

## Notes

- The bundled schema is based on Adobe Commerce 2.4.7 (current LTS).
- Use introspection to understand available fields before writing mutations.
- For live data queries, use the actual Commerce GraphQL endpoint directly with the
  credentials from your project's component `.env` file.
